# CCVAA multi-agent OS (shared)

## Roles

| Role | Primary contact | Owns |
|------|-----------------|------|
| Product Manager | Human CEO | Scope, priorities, advice, product docs |
| Developer | PM (via handoff) | Feature branches, PRs, implementation |
| QA | PM (via handoff) | Pass 1 / Pass 2 / baseline; single-Send OTP + CEO; Preview bypass via `.env.local` |

CEO talks primarily to the **Product Manager**. Repo docs are the shared brain — not chat history.

## Canonical docs

- `AGENTS.md` — OS overview
- `docs/product/FEATURES.md` — living feature inventory (PM maintains)
- `docs/product/ROADMAP.md` — Now / Next / Later
- `docs/protocols/` — communication, handoff, GIT_DEPLOY, QA_AUTH, **PREVIEW_PROTECTION**
- `docs/templates/` — bug, feature, QA, handoff templates

## Environments (agent Dev/QA)

- Dev: http://localhost:3000/
- Preview: Vercel URL for the feature branch/PR (pre-merge; **Deployment Protection** — bypass via `.env.local`)
- Production: https://ccvaa-web.vercel.app/ (`main` — QA Pass 2)
- **Out of agent flow:** https://ccvaa.ca/ — CEO manual only (DNS/cache)

Default ship path: feature branch → QA Preview → merge → QA on `ccvaa-web.vercel.app`. See `docs/protocols/GIT_DEPLOY.md`.

## Hard constraints

- Never commit secrets (`.env.local`, credentials, OTP codes, `VERCEL_AUTOMATION_BYPASS_SECRET`)
- Commit / push / merge only when CEO explicitly asks
- Prefer feature branches + PRs over direct pushes to `main`
- Prefer small, focused changes; do not over-engineer
- Agents do not use `ccvaa.ca` for Dev/QA passes
- Next.js 16 differs from older Next — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before novel APIs; use `proxy.ts` not deprecated `middleware.ts`
